# UI component authoring standards

Quick-reference for coding standards when working in `packages/ui/src/components/`.
For step-by-step create / edit / delete workflows and test patterns, use **`$ui-authoring`**.

---

## Variant pattern

| Layer | Pattern |
| ----- | ------- |
| Primitives | `cva()` — `export const xyzClasses = cva("...", { variants: { … } })` |
| Blocks / templates | Plain function — `export const xyzClasses = (props): string => cn(…)` |

Never use `cva()` in blocks or templates — they have no CVA variant grid to assert.

## Token prefix

Only CSS vars using `cssVarPrefix` from `packages/tokens/src/generators/generator.config.ts`
(currently `lex`, e.g. `--lex-button-radius`) are allowed in `*.variants.ts`.

```ts
// Good
"bg-(--lex-button-primary-background)"

// Bad — raw Tailwind palette
"bg-blue-500"
```

`pnpm ui:check` (includes `ui:audit`) enforces this — raw palette literals fail the build.

## className merging

```ts
// Static class merging — use cn()
cn("base-class", conditionalClass, props.className)

// Stateful Base UI className callback — use mergeClassName()
className: mergeClassName("base-class", props.className)
```

`mergeClassName()` is only for Base UI `className` prop callbacks that receive a state
object. Use `cn()` everywhere else.

## ref pattern

```ts
// New components — React 19 ref prop (no forwardRef needed)
export const Button = ({ ref, ...props }: ButtonProps) => { … }

// Existing components — keep forwardRef; do not refactor unless explicitly requested
export const Button = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>((props, ref) => { … })

// .types.ts — always declare explicit ref type
export interface ButtonProps extends React.ComponentPropsWithoutRef<"button"> {
  ref?: React.Ref<HTMLButtonElement>
}
```

## Layer export rules

| Layer | Export from `packages/ui/src/index.ts` |
| ----- | ------------------------------------- |
| Primitives | Yes — required |
| Blocks | No — registry-first; consumers install via `lexsys add` |
| Templates | No — registry-first; consumers install via `lexsys add` |

## Locked decisions (CS.4)

- Nav items (`SidebarItemLink`, `SidebarItemButton`) use plain `<a>` / `<button>` — **not** the `Button` primitive. Their styling requirements differ and they own their own appearance.
- `SidebarTrigger` is composable — place it inside any `<Sidebar>` descendant; `Drawer` context wraps the root `<aside>` so any descendant `DrawerTrigger` auto-wires.

## Registry templates — never edit directly

`packages/registry/templates/` is **generated output**. Always edit
`packages/ui/src/components/` and run `pnpm registry:sync` to propagate.
Manual edits to registry templates will be overwritten on the next sync.

## Post-edit

```sh
pnpm ui:check       # lint + typecheck + audit + tests
pnpm registry:sync  # propagates UI changes to registry templates
pnpm ui:test        # tests only (fast re-run)
pnpm format
```

Full checklists and test patterns → **`$ui-authoring`**.
